gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Knicks 121, Wizards 105
gameRecap.excerpt: The Knicks defeated the Wizards, 121-105. Julius Randle recorded a game-high 39 points along with seven rebounds and five assists for the Knicks, with Jalen Brunson adding 33 points and eight assists in the victory. Kyle Kuzma tallied 27 points and two assists for the Wizards in the losing effort. The Knicks have won four in a row and improve to 21-15 in the regular season, while the Wizards fall 6-29.
